Let 

\begin{align*}
c = \sup_{f} \int_{0}^{1} (f(t)^{3}+|f(t)|)dt
\end{align*}
where supremum is taken over all integrable functions $f : [0,1] \to \mathbb{R}$ such that $\int_{0}^{1}f(t)dt=-10$, $\int_{0}^{1} f^{2}(t)dt=100+\frac{1}{12}$, and 
\begin{align*}
\sup_{J \subset [0,1]} \frac{1}{|J|}\int_{J}\left|f(t) - \frac{1}{|J|}\int_{J}f(s)ds \right|^{2}dt \leq \frac{1}{12},
\end{align*}
where supremum is taken over all subintervals $J \subset [0,1]$. Here $|J|$ denotes the length of the interval. 


Find $c+\frac{1985}{2}$.

